HEADWORD: Aspergillum
<hw>As`per*gil"lum</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>aspergillum</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>aspergere</ets>. See <er>Asperse</er>, v. t.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The brush used in the Roman Catholic church for
sprinkling holy water on the people.</def> <altsp>[Also written
<it>aspergillus</it>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>See <er>Wateringpot
shell</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aspergilliform</ent>⟦br⟧
